<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<Pathway xmlns="http://pathvisio.org/GPML/2013a" Name="Small cell lung cancer" Data-Source="WikiPathways" Version="WP4658_r142502" Author="[Khanspers, MaintBot, Fehrhart, Finterly, Egonw, Eweitz, Ash iyer]" Last-Modified="20260311224642" Organism="Homo sapiens">
  <Comment Source="WikiPathways-description">Small cell lung carcinoma (SCLC) is a highly malignant cancer of the lung.

Genes altered in small cell lung carcinoma:
1. TP53 is mutated in 70-90% of SCLCs. 
2. RB1 is inactivated in most SCLCs. 
3. PTEN is mutated in 2-10% of SCLCs. 
4. MYC amplifications and amplification of MYC family members is found in 30% of SCLCs. 
5. FHIT protein expression is lost due to loss of heterozygocity (LOH) on chromosome arm 3p found in more than 80% of SCLCs. 

This description was adapted from [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Small-cell_carcinoma). 
Phosphorylation sites were added based on information from [PhosphoSitePlus (R)](https://www.phosphosite.org].</Comment>
